author: Inside Edition
description: Michael Marraccini says he met podcaster Laura Owens in 2016 and after two months of casual dating, he says Owens told him she was pregnant with twins by him. He says Owens bombarded him with fake pregnancy tests and claims of having had unsuccessful abortions. Six months later, Marraccini claims Owens admitted to making up multiple pregnancies. Owens denies Marraccini's claims. She faces 14 felony counts alleging she committed fraud and perjury against two other men. Owens has pleaded not guilty.
title: Man Says Woman Falsely Accused Him Of Getting Her Pregnant With Twins

author: Inside Edition
description: Coast-to-coast nurses are expressing outrage after they are no longer being considered a "profession." It all has to go with how the One Big Beautiful Bill changes the nation's student loan program. By not being classified as professionals, nurses are limited on how much money they can borrow to pursue their graduate degree. The cap is at $100,000. The concern is that this could lead to an even greater nursing shortage.
title: Outrage After Nursing Is No Longer Considered A Profession

author: Inside Edition
description: Authorities say Virginia high school football coach Travis Turner, who has gone missing, is wanted for allegedly possessing child pornography. Police say Turner disappeared when they were on their way to his home as part of an investigation. They would not say what the allegations were, but it was revealed Tuesday that he's sought on five child pornography arrest warrants. Turner, 46, disappeared last week and is now "considered a fugitive," police said Tuesday.
title: Missing Football Coach Now Considered Fugitive, Police Say

author: Inside Edition
description: Oz Pearlman has been blowing minds while promoting his new book. He's stunning the top names in the news business by seemingly reading their minds, guessing their dream guests, and even their ATM pin codes. Inside Edition's Lisa Guerrero met with Pearlman in 2015 after his big break on "America's Got Talent." Guerrero analyzed part of his routine with renowned mentalist Mark Edward, where he asked judges to guess how many gumballs were in a jar.
title: Oz Pearlman Blows Minds On TV While Promoting His New Book

author: Inside Edition
description: Tatiana Schlossberg wrote in a New Yorker essay, published on the 62nd anniversary of JFK's assassination, that she found out she has acute myeloid leukemia.
title: JFK's Granddaughter Has Terminal Cancer #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A rare Superman comic found in an attic just became the most expensive comic book in the world, fetching $9.12 million at auction. The comic book in question was "Superman No. 1," published by Detective Comics Inc. in 1939. There are estimated to be fewer than 500 copies in existence. It had been tucked away for decades, in a cardboard box, under a bunch of old newspapers. That may have preserved it – its condition was graded at a 9, on a one to ten scale.
title: Brothers Find Incredibly Rare Superman Comic In Mom's Attic

author: Inside Edition
description: Forget politics. This is the real hot topic that's going to start fights at Thanksgiving dinner this year: sweet potato pie or pumpkin pie? A bakery in Mississippi says they're making plenty of both to prevent any families from falling out. The owner says aside from their main ingredients, the pies are very different. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Families Fear Fallout Over Thanksgiving Question: Sweet Potato Or Pumpkin Pie?

author: Inside Edition
description: Twenty-six-year-old business analyst Bethany Magee was set on fire during a horrific attack on a commuter train in Chicago. Police say a man poured gasoline over Magee on a Chicago L train.
title: Who Was The Woman Set On Fire In Chicago Train Attack?
